    <stitle>9 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RT-8609 SERIES - REMOVE - CLUTCH HOUSING</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="2">
        <title>CLUTCH HOUSING</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>For models so equipped, remove the clutch release mechanism and/or clutch brake assembly.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the two bolts and six nuts with lockwashers from the studs that secure the clutch
                housing to the transmission case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302929">inset, Figure 29</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302929" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302929" filename="../figg13/g1302929.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 29. Remove Bolts and Nuts From Studs Securing Clutch Housing to Transmission Case
                </caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Jar the clutch housing with a rubber mallet to break the gasket seal and pull from the
                transmission case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302930">Figure 30</hotlnk>). Remove the gasket (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302930">inset</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302930" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302930" filename="../figg13/g1302930.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 30. Break Gasket Seal and Remove Gasket</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
